text: General elections were held for the first time in Cambodia on 1 September 1946.Dieter Nohlen, Florian Grotz & Christof Hartmann (2001) Elections in Asia: A data handbook, Volume II, p69 The Democratic Party won 50 of the 67 seats, with voter turnout estimated to be 60%.Nohlen et al., p64 ==Results== {| class="wikitable" |colspan=9|300px |- ! colspan="2" style="text-align: center; font-weight:bold;" | Party ! style="text-align: center; font- weight:bold;" | Votes ! style="text-align: center; font-weight:bold;" | % ! style="text-align: center; font-weight:bold;" | Seats |- | style="background- color:#800080; color:#800080;" | | Democratic Party | | style="text-align: right;" | 73.5 | style="text-align: right;" | 50 |- | style="background- color:#FAAC58; color:#FAAC58;" | | Liberal Party | | style="text-align: right;" | | style="text-align: right;" | 14 |- | style="background- color:#A0A0A0;" | | Independents | | style="text-align: right;" | | style="text-align: right;" | 3 |- | | Invalid/Blank votes | | style="text- align: right;" | – | style="text-align: right;" | – |- | colspan="2" style="font-weight:bold;" | Total | | style="text-align: right;" | 100 | style="text-align: right;" | 67 |- | colspan="5" | Source: Nohlen et al. |} ==References== Category:1946 elections in Asia Category:Elections in Cambodia Category:1946 in Cambodia
